Reviews.Title: Good for price
Reviews.Author: Alaa
Reviews.Content: Nice shape, very good keyboard design, it's not the best laptop in the market for sure, If you are looking to play the latest heavy duty 3D games, for sure you should look for something else, but for daily use, Internet with multi tabs on the browser, Chat software, Skype, Play basic games, type word documents, spreed sheets, it's very useful. Yes if you compare some other laptops with this one, they may load the operating system faster with one or two seconds, and run the other software faster with 1 sec, but for sure that does not bother me for the price I spend on this laptop, in another word, this one second faster thing does not worth to pay extra $100 or around.It has 2GB of RAM, and 320GB of HDD storage space, for me, no need for more than 2GB of RAM, (and now i'm already opening 13 tab on my internet browser + Skype + watching movie all at the same time ), and for the storage space, it's fair enough, and in future if I need more space, i will get external HDD).Anyone who want a low price laptop with a good shape, nice quality, good branded name, this should be the choose.I tried to check the Asus website for drivers for this product ( as type of checking for future needs and there services, and I found at [...] ) that this product does not need any drivers if you are using Windows 8 32bit, that means all drivers already included in Windows OS.

Reviews.Title: performs well
Reviews.Author: Jim MacLaury
Reviews.Content: All is well with this product except for the touchpad, and that may be more me than anything else. I have never really liked or gotten used to touchpads, so will use this laptop with a mouse. Good price on this unit, and I have no regrets.

Reviews.Title: You get what you pay for
Reviews.Author: Xavier
Reviews.Content: Well I just ordered this computer two days ago and it came today. Truthfully I didn't know what to expect. I've spent sometime getting used to the operating system and getting a feel for the computer. So far I like it and Windows 8 is not as bad as some make it out to be. I am satisfied with the computer and it was at a fair price. However this computer lags a lot and is very slow at times.. I was looking into buying a beefier laptop but I believe this will be good enough for now. If your looking for a fast computer this is not for you. It's very light (cheaply made) but nice.

Reviews.Title: Cannot beat the price for this standard quality!!!
Reviews.Author: DrknLovly
Reviews.Content: This is definitely NOT a gaming computer but any PC aficionado should know that by now. This computer is for a very laid-back user or media buff or even college student. If you're on a budget, don't care to have all the bells and whistles (touchscreen capability, rotating screen, 500GB+ HDD, etc. and latest Intel system) and just need something that WORKS, then i would definitely say get this one as a starter especially if you're still not too sold on those Linux-based Chromebooks. Personally, I've had this PC for a couple months and so far I've run into no major issues. All pc's crash eventually so just make sure to invest in a proper external hard drive and you'll do just fine. Windows 8 isn't really all as hellish as people made it out to be and again i don't even have a touch screen and i still don't find it that annoying. Setup was pretty straightforward and easy. It updates alot so expect that like every 2-3 days for so called "important updates" so you obviously can't use the computer at that time but it usually doesn't take that long. All in all for the PRICE i paid for it and i got in 2 days time, what more can you ask for as a trusty notebook pc?

Reviews.Title: Good bang for your buck
Reviews.Author: Joylynn Moore
Reviews.Content: I love everything about this laptop. The Windows 8 takes a little patience getting used to but besides that. Its excellent!

Reviews.Title: Great deal
Reviews.Author: Gina Lindow
Reviews.Content: It is a great deal for an actual laptop.I didn't have super high expectations, and don't need anything fancy. I've had no troubles with it so far. Its not quite as sturdy as my old HP laptop, and a little "noisy." Still, for the money, best deal ever.

Reviews.Title: Great for price
Reviews.Author: Jw "jw"
Reviews.Content: I have another low end ASUS and continue to have a great experience with it. I plan to use this new one as a back up computer. It was fast enough and easy to use right out of the box. Then, I downloaded Office 365 and the system was sluggish. I uninstalled the software and it is much better again.When camping I run out of battery charge and need a second computer so I can continue writing. Wordpad, which is already installed, meets my needs under these circumstances. Yes, I know I could get a back-up battery for the other computer, but this newer one has a longer battery life than the old one and it has a cd drive, unlike the old one. Happy, but only rated 4 since it couldn't handle Office 365.

Reviews.Title: ASUS Laptop
Reviews.Author: Clerk
Reviews.Content: I had to take this on a recent trip and loved it.  Light weight, but quick, easy to use and fast.

Reviews.Title: great computer!!  never had a problem with asus motherboards!!  hoping there computers are just as good!!
Reviews.Author: fred hill
Reviews.Content: some what heavier than what I am use to,  but I will get over it!!  love it!!  windows 8 is alright..  I was on the internet in less than 5 minutes out of the box!! very easy to use!!

Reviews.Title: Great value for the money
Reviews.Author: Shadow Queen
Reviews.Content: Very happy with the computer and it came with a great price tag (considerably better than an HP!!).  Just wish it didn't have Windows 8.

Reviews.Title: recomment this latop
Reviews.Author: ALVARO MENDOZA
Reviews.Content: the latop is working very well , I liked and recommend this produt. is especial tool for college and the price is really good

Reviews.Title: Worth the price
Reviews.Author: n. edvalds
Reviews.Content: This is an excellent basic laptop for the casual user (not for people who do any sort of programing and intense gaming). I was very impressed by how well this works for how little I spent. Adobe products can be used on this for design with decent viewing, but it is obvious that it doesn't have the graphics of a computer built for that use.

Reviews.Title: Packaging Size
Reviews.Author: Russel
Reviews.Content: I was charged a lot because the box it came in was big. No issues otherwise. It works really well.

Reviews.Title: Still learning how to use my laptop
Reviews.Author: william raines
Reviews.Content: I am still learning how to use my laptop and I feel that when I get moreknowledge on how to use my laptop and find out more about it functionsI will like it more.

Reviews.Title: nice computer
Reviews.Author: Amazon Customer
Reviews.Content: I purchased this for my mother in law who has never used a computer but loves playing games on my computer when she visits.  The computer itself is great but I dont recommend Windows 8 to anyone. It is very difficult to use.  The packaging was great, the computer is very easy to use itself.  Great buy for the money so far.

Reviews.Title: Features of computer
Reviews.Author: Syed Noorullah
Reviews.Content: It is good and easy to operate.key board is comfortable.shspe is attractive and screen touch system is also charming and enjoyable.

Reviews.Title: Great computer for the money, but don't upgrade to Windows 8.1.
Reviews.Author: William E Luedeker
Reviews.Content: I've had this computer for a couple of months and am basically very pleased, especially for the price.  You pretty much have to add more ram to get a decent speed from the computer (runs fine with 4 gig).  It took a few days to get used to Windows 8.  The only problem I've had was when I upgraded to Windows 8.1--when you close the lid and put the computer to sleep, it won't start back up when you open the lid.  The only way to get it working is to remove/reinstall the battery and restart it.  After a couple of frustrating days of this routine, I reinstalled the original Windows 8 OS and everything is fine again.  It's kinda flimsy compared to my wife's older ASUS laptop, but it's a really good computer at a very reasonable price.

Reviews.Title: Functional but has an annoyance
Reviews.Author: nancy mishler
Reviews.Content: There are several things I like about this computer. The size and windows 8  There is an annoyance that I hate about this computer. When I type the cursor defauts back to the beginning of the sentence.or the middle of the sentence.  I can't tell you how many times throughout my day that I go through this.  It happened just now. I haven't identified the why yet.  This computer is functional and performs my day to day routine.

Reviews.Title: fairly good product
Reviews.Author: Valrie Telesford
Reviews.Content: have to get used to it.  when typing script, the curser goes elsewhere and jumbles up the script and I have to be typing it over.  I guess I have to get used to it..  However the price is good..

Reviews.Title: Great for the price..
Reviews.Author: Onica W.
Reviews.Content: I bought this laptop for my niece a few months ago and it is working great. I have had issues with laptop in that price range over heating or low battery life but, no problem with this laptop. It use to take a long time to boot up but I added to gis of RAM and problem solve.

Reviews.Title: Extremely Slow
Reviews.Author: txzee
Reviews.Content: My household needed a new computer and I read the reviews before purchasing this one.  We don't do anything major, simple surfing, powerpoints, and a few games.  My computer will freeze or shut down without warning.  I have never seen so many extra popups before. I can't say that I enjoy this computer and although it was on the lower price end for computers, I feel like my money was wasted.

Reviews.Title: asus computer
Reviews.Author: Don Pittaway
Reviews.Content: Good computer just wonder if it had windows 8 recovery discs that should have been included with it. But good deal this is a 400 dollar plus unit in the major retail store.

Reviews.Title: Asus
Reviews.Author: Linda Taylor
Reviews.Content: I like the laptop, but am not familiar with Windows 8.  So it is taking time to get familiar with the product

Reviews.Title: Nice and swift
Reviews.Author: Charlotte Sullivan
Reviews.Content: A online student wish! I like the new modernized pace and programs! I just got to get used to a newer model laptop!

Reviews.Title: laptop
Reviews.Author: Willie Turner
Reviews.Content: I purchased it for my grand daughter.  She love it and it meet all the needs for school this year.

Reviews.Title: Laptop Crashed In 2 Months!!!
Reviews.Author: JJ
Reviews.Content: I needed a laptop quick and I decided to use this Asus laptop because of the cost and the prime shipping. I had a virus protection on it and one day I started the laptop and the laptop didn't start. I talked to the Asus company and they wouldn't take it back because I purchased it on amazon. I blew $300 bucks!!!

Reviews.Title: Get what you pay for
Reviews.Author: rotorhead9
Reviews.Content: I purchased this laptop as a cheap light duty travel computer.  It is just that. The price was right Amazon delivered in a timely manner. Window 8 is the worst I've ever worked with and will replace it with and older operating system.  The processor is a little slow but will meet my requirements for word processing and email.

Reviews.Title: For my personal
Reviews.Author: Alison Alexander
Reviews.Content: I can't believe it. My new Asus 15.6 laptop. I don't know much about computers but my neighbour does and told me this is a high end product. It has all the features as was advertised and I am more than pleased with its performance.It is more than I expected. The keyboard is awesome because the prints are big and is easy to use. I am getting accustomed to windows 8 and I am always for improvement.I love the weight, size and the screen is awesome. It is easy to set up. And by the way it does not get hot when in use. I love my Asus laptop.

Reviews.Title: Good Price
Reviews.Author: Carlos
Reviews.Content: first time I use a laptop asus and satisfied because it is fast and quality resolution of the screen is excellent, the keyboard is sturdy, has windows 8 and this makes it easier to use. Excellent quality in relation to price $ 280, these are the items for which I like to shop at Amazon and hope that the company continue to make these types of sales items good quality low price. thanks

Reviews.Title: laptop for school
Reviews.Author: Lester Smith
Reviews.Content: I bought this for my grand child one here graduation from high school she was thrilled. And so was I the computer had a good range of extras ,and worked good ,computer had windows 8 witch took a lot of reconfigure to make it usable for school.

Reviews.Title: great computer
Reviews.Author: Michelle
Reviews.Content: I gave this rating because it is a nice sturdy computer. Speed is nice, but windows 8 was hard to get use to.

Reviews.Title: Good for the Price
Reviews.Author: Eanderson
Reviews.Content: Purchased this on sale for family use.  The machine is good enough for the price for general use but really miss not having a backlit keyboard.  Everyone HATES Windows 8 so it is slowly being used more and more but we may wind up reloading the operating system.

Reviews.Title: Big screen
Reviews.Author: Ginny Katsourides
Reviews.Content: I bought this laptop on the recommendation of my daughter who had just purchased an ASUS computer. I really like the big screen-just haven't had time to set up all my preferences.

Reviews.Title: cheap
Reviews.Author: tango
Reviews.Content: First is amazons pricing, they had this on a special saying it was nearly 60 off in price, only to find it listed after the lightening deal for a mere ten off....games, games, games...one need be wary of amazon pricing. The computer is cheaply made, more or less unattractive, the sides of the keyboard and the mouse pad give way under pressure..the keyboard keys stroke is awkward. Mine was returned...better to spend a bit more and get something more solid and reliable. I would rather doubt that this laptop can withstand much handling and transporting...short-lived i would guess.

Reviews.Title: Not a good purchase
Reviews.Author: Ignacio
Reviews.Content: I bought this computer form the Warehouse Deals, and it's not "like new", I've been dealing with some software issues, and the computer really goes slow.However. the display size is great.

Reviews.Title: Don't like it all all
Reviews.Author: Joe
Reviews.Content: There isn't a lot I like about this laptop. Cost was probably the only thing I do like. When you open an app it takes about 45 seconds to open. The layout of the keyboard is off so it takes a while to get used to. Battery does not last as long as advertised. Too many other things to list. Trying to sell it and get something different.

Reviews.Title: Not working
Reviews.Author: AetnaJo
Reviews.Content: I have used this PC only 5-6 times @ it's not working. What a bummer. Hopefully I can get it replaced or get my money back.

Reviews.Title: Excellent laptop for $280
Reviews.Author: Rob
Reviews.Content: The laptop has performed great so far, especially considering its price ($280!!). Perfect laptop for a basic pc user (internet, email, word processing, etc.). Amazon also has some conflicting descriptions on which processor this includes. This model includesthe Intel Celeron B830 (1.8GHz) Sandy Bridge, NOT the AMD A4. Overall, I would absolutely recommend this laptop, thin and fairly lightweight considering it's size. It is also very well built, very solid feel and nice big keys with big lettering. Bought for my father who has some eye sight issues and this works great!

Reviews.Title: Stay from this turtle, Asus should be Ashamed of this product
Reviews.Author: BEAR_CUB
Reviews.Content: This machine runs moves slower than a turtle. Maybe I just got a lemon I don't know. I have bought several of the lower end Asus laptops over the last few years from Amazon and have been satisfied with them up until this particular model. I wish I could return this for something different. I don't have high expectations when it comes to laptop performance, I am just looking for something that provides consistency and reliability for internet surfing, listening to music, and light MS office work. Asus should be ashamed of selling such a product.

Reviews.Title: Just OK
Reviews.Author: Ed
Reviews.Content: Asus makes the most affordable laptops right now- this one feels a bit flimsy but if you treat it well it will be fine.  My main gripe is that Asus included a 10 key number pad on the right of the keyboard.  So then they place the mouse pad over to the left- this forces your hands to be off set to the left.  I feel off center when I use this as my hands keep feeling like they are about to fall off the left side of the keyboard.  There is no divider between the left and right mouse buttons on the pad- so I always have to look down when something isn't clicking right.You don't need a 10key number pad on a laptop- this addition forced them to make some bad design choices.  Wished I could return but it's too much of a headache.  And 2GB of ram is pretty weak, you can get at least 4GB in comparably priced units.  And don't get me started on Windows 8...

Reviews.Title: basic dedicated laptop
Reviews.Author: reugenen
Reviews.Content: It was inexpensive Windows 8 laptop with wireless (about $100 more than Windows 8).Only use a few programs with downloads from remote location.Has worked flawlessly, no speed, no storage, links quickly.It could use a mouse the touch pad (not a touch screen) is a little sensitive.

Reviews.Title: Computer Works Well
Reviews.Author: Niki
Reviews.Content: It takes some time to get use to the track pad, but you will get used to it. HOWEVER my laptop started to force me ton restart it every 2 minutes. It is currently in a computer repair shop. I have not even had it a month.....

Reviews.Title: ASUS is the best so they say
Reviews.Author: Amazon Customer
Reviews.Content: I understand that once in a while a person receives a lemon and it was my turn. You should thank me because it could have been you. The first three weeks should have been a clue that there was trouble lurking in this machine. At times I could not turn it on the next day. I would take the battery out, wait a little and then put it back in. Then I could turn it on. Battery showed that it was charged so some other power issue. Then the touch pad claimed to be error resistant, according to the specifications and the sticker on the computer. But it kept moving my cursor around, creating errors. No button to turn off the pad but reading the manual, it says use the function F9 sequence. Nothing. So I chatted with a rep and downloaded the latest. Once I did that, I was able to turn the pad off. But it added a new problem, it would shut off at random. No warnings. Blink. Off. I turn it on and before it gets to the Windows 8.0 start screen, it shuts off again. Then at times I would get it to last maybe 2 hours, then off she goes. By now I have missed the window of opportunity to send it back...sigh. I call, and after a painful long call, it was determined I have a "deeper" problem and have to send it back. Now I am out of a computer except my older machine. Not to mention it ran slower than my 5 year old machine. Mistake to purchase this machine. Sorry, it is how I feel. Maybe it is just a lemon and need to resolve the issue.

Reviews.Title: Waste of money... do not buy
Reviews.Author: Mark Twain "book maven"
Reviews.Content: Worst of the worst... it is so slow... it can drive you crazy.... and the mouse pad is working only 50% of the time... very frustrating... save yourself the hassle and do not buy this product. and window 8 compare to window 7 is so bad... each newer version of windows takes you back a hundred steps closer to stone age.

Reviews.Title: not good
Reviews.Author: Thao Yang
Reviews.Content: I'd always owned Asus laptop, but to be honest this laptop is really bad. I don't know what Asus was think when they put out this laptop.Cons- super slow you can barely watch youtube videos with this laptop- very hard to navigate with windows 8- track pad makes it even harder to navigatePro- you get a laptop a very low price (that's all i can think of)

Reviews.Title: I bought this for my wife
Reviews.Author: William Crant
Reviews.Content: Having windows 8, I do not personally like the new platform, but my wife does so that's the main thing

Reviews.Title: too slow
Reviews.Author: madeorakouma bahomda
Reviews.Content: this laptop doesn't come with Windows 8 office and i had to buy it too expensive.  this laptop is too slow.

Reviews.Title: operating system didn't work
Reviews.Author: Lynn Q. Griffin "amazon fan"
Reviews.Content: I bought this laptop, and was pleased with the price. I purchased it on 10/18/13, received it on 10/24/13 (so far, so good, huh?). I was learning the Windows 8 operating system, and by 10/30/13, the computer no longer worked (wouldn't connect with the internet no matter what I did).Paid $75.00 for a diagnostic check, and was told it was the Windows 8 that was not functioning properly; was advised to contact Microsoft for a repair disc. I did, and they said, nope - not covered. Call Asus. Called Asus support; they said, "sorry not covered under warranty, but for the low price of $149.00 we can fix the Windows 8 system and sell you Microsoft Office and anti-virus". REALLY? Luckily I called Amazon, who said that it was under their warranty. They are sending me another one. If this happens again, I'll assume that Asus has a scam going and want to get more money out of you.So far, not very impressed.(But thank you Amazon for covering this product for 30 days!!)

Reviews.Title: WORST COMPUTER EVER
Reviews.Author: David Melahn
Reviews.Content: First one was supposed to be new but received a used broken one that amazon replaced. The second one has been returned to ASUS for repair in two months and must call ASUS on a daily basis to get tech help to make it work. REALLY A WASTE OF MY PENSION MONEY. WOULD NOT RECOMMEND TO MY WORST ENEMY

Reviews.Title: Unit underpowered and poorly planned, Windows 8 the worst.
Reviews.Author: luee
Reviews.Content: Unit came on time. It was a price purchase just as my Compaq 15.6 died. Keyboard is a nice size and works well, with just a bit of a bounce. Screen is nice and bright with a decent lateral and horizontal view. Problems right off the bat with explorer, froze and would not recover, the installed RAM is too little for that browser. Installed both chrome and FF and both worked well for a time or two. Than they also froze. Machine shut down and could not repair itself. Sent a message asking to clean itself and start all over. Hmm perfect time to send back.Cannot say enough negatives about windows 8. Seems to have been designed by the devil for tablet morons. Nothing is intuitive for the experienced laptop user. Floating tiles, hidden menus and basics like on and off nowhere to be found. A forced consumer with little choice. So I am rating the unit and Windows a big one. Cannot go lower.
